    "We treat these outputs as communication behaviors constrained by prompts and training, not as direct measures of internal states.",
    "Our approach builds on emerging work that adapts psychometric instruments for language models to probe response styles, stability, and calibration across tasks 13.",
    "Because we interpret these scores against human benchmarks, we anchor them to canonical GSES norms (pooled adult M = 29.55, SD = 5.32, with cross-national means ranging 20.22 to 33.19 [e.g., Japan ≈ 20.22; Costa Rica ≈ 33.19]) 22.",
    "We, therefore, use the GSES as a standardized scaffold to compare models and tasks, and to examine how self-efficacy aligns, or fails to align, with task performance.",
    "The primary objective of this study is to evaluate the simulated self-assessment capabilities of LLMs using the GSES."
